tl.lin.data.map

Class HMapKL<K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • tl.lin.data.map.HMapKL<K>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the type of keys maintained by this map
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, MapKL<K>

    public class HMapKL<K>
extends Object
implements MapKL<K>, Cloneable, Serializable
    Hash-based implementation of the MapKL interface. MapKL is a specialized variant the standard Java Map interface, except that the values are hard coded as floats for efficiency reasons (keys can be arbitrary objects). This implementation was adapted from HashMap version 1.73, 03/13/07.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        Constructs a new HMapKL with the same mappings as the specified MapKL. The HMapKL is created with default load factor (0.75) and an initial capacity sufficient to hold the mappings in the specified MapKL.
        Parameters:

        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified map is null

      • values

        public Collection<Long> values()
        Description copied from interface: MapKL
        Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map. Note that this is a inefficient operation since it triggers autoboxing of the long values, which is exactly what this implementation is trying to avoid. Unlike a standard Java Map, values in the backing map cannot be altered with this collection view.
        Specified by:
        values in interface MapKL<K>
        Returns:
        a collection view of the values contained in this map
